<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11119a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11119a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11119a"> 119(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> la pondreuse famille / des sourds</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Avant-Propos</b> Ces <i>M&eacute;moires</i> ont &eacute;t&eacute; l&apos;objet de ma pr&eacute;dilection: saint Bonaventure obtint du ciel la permission de continuer les siens apr&egrave;s sa mort; je n&apos;esp&egrave;re pas une telle faveur, mais je d&eacute;sirerais ressusciter &agrave; l&apos;heure des fant&ocirc;mes, pour corriger au moins les &eacute;preuves. Au surplus, quand l&apos;Eternit&eacute; m&apos;aura de ses deux mains bouch&eacute; les oreilles, dans <mark><i>la poudreuse famille des sourds</i></mark>, je n&apos;entendrai plus personne. <font color="green">[Preface: These <i>Memoirs</i> have been the object of my predilection. St Bonaventure obtained from heaven permission to continue his after death. I have no hope of such favour, but I would like to come back to life at the time of ghosts, if only to correct the proofs. Furthermore, when Eternity has stopped my ears with both its hands, <mark>among the dusty family of the deaf</mark>, I will no longer hear anyone.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i>M&eacute;moires d&apos;outre-tombe</i> 13</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
